<item>
            <title>[LU-8694] ZFS format fails when /etc/hostid is set or unset. </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8694</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Attempting to format ZFS OSTs we see the following error:&lt;br/&gt;
mkfs.lustre FATAL: spl_hostid not set. See mkfs.lustre(8)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We attempt to set hostid by using /sbin/genhostid, we confirm the ID exists, same failure. We attempt to set hostid by /usr/bin/hostid, confirm the ID exists, same failure&lt;br/&gt;
At this time we cannot format OSTS, system is dead.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="40472">LU-8694</key>
